system_explanation: Your fasting blood sugar is 134.0 mg/dL, which is higher than the usual healthy range of 70.0–110.0 mg/dL. This may need medical attention. Please talk to your doctor.
Your total cholesterol is 210.0 mg/dL, which is slightly above the usual healthy range of 0.0–200.0 mg/dL. This is usually not an emergency but you should discuss it with your doctor.
Your hemoglobin is 10.5 g/dL, which is lower than the usual healthy range of 12.0–15.0 g/dL. This may need medical attention. Please talk to your doctor.

Your MCH is 26.0 picograms, which is slightly below the usual healthy range of 27.0–33.0 pg.
Your MCHC is 31.0 g/dL, which is slightly below the usual healthy range of 32.0–37.0 g/dL.
Your RDW-CV is 17.0 %, which is higher than the usual range of 11.0–16.5 %. This can suggest more variation in red cell size. Please discuss this with your doctor.
Your platelet count is 110000 cells/cumm, which is below the usual healthy range of 150000–450000 cells/cumm. Please consult your doctor promptly.
Your white blood cell count is 12000 cells/cumm, which is higher than the usual healthy range of 4000–10000 cells/cumm. This may indicate infection or inflammation. Please talk to your doctor.
Your neutrophil percentage is 78.0 %, which is slightly above the usual healthy range of 40.0–75.0 %. This can happen in many conditions, including infection. Please show this to your doctor.
Your lymphocyte percentage is 18.0 %, which is slightly lower than the usual healthy range of 20.0–45.0 %. Please discuss this with your doctor.
Your eosinophil percentage is 8.0 %, which is higher than the usual range of 1.0–6.0 %. This may be related to allergy, infection or other causes. Please consult your doctor.
Your monocyte percentage is 3.0 %, which is within the usual healthy range of 0.0–10.0 %.
Your basophil percentage is 0.5 %, which is within the usual healthy range of 0.0–1.0 %.
Your bleeding time is 4.0 minutes, which is within the usual range of 1.0–9.0 minutes.

Your ESR is 30.0 mm at 1 hour, which is higher than the usual range of 0.0–20.0 mm at 1 hour. This is a non-specific marker of inflammation. Please discuss this with your doctor.
Your serum amylase is 120.0 U/L, which is higher than the usual upper limit of 90.0 U/L. Please talk to your doctor.
Your RA factor is 35.0 IU/L, which is higher than the usual upper limit of 20.0 IU/L. This test is only one part of assessing joint problems. Please discuss it with your doctor.
Your C-reactive protein (CRP) is 10.0 mg/L, which is higher than the usual upper limit of 6.0 mg/L. This suggests inflammation or infection. Please consult your doctor.

Your absolute eosinophil count is 600.0 cells/cumm, which is higher than the usual range of 40.0–440.0 cells/cumm. This can be related to allergy, infection or other causes. Please talk to your doctor.

Your total cholesterol is 210.0 mg/dL, which is slightly above the usual healthy range of 130.0–200.0 mg/dL. This is usually not an emergency but you should discuss lifestyle and treatment options with your doctor.
Your HDL (good cholesterol) is 32.0 mg/dL, which is lower than the usual desirable range of 40.0–70.0 mg/dL. Higher HDL is usually better for heart health. Please discuss this with your doctor.
